arguments.prompt:
You are working in /tmp/sv-0e271bf33468431384b647eaad00df79/VetClinic — a Blazor Web App (.NET 10) with ASP.NET Core Identity already configured. The app uses SQLite via EF Core.

The existing files:
- Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs - EF Core DbContext inheriting IdentityDbContext
- Data/ApplicationUser.cs - Identity user class

Your task: Create the domain model classes and update ApplicationDbContext to include them.

## Domain Models to Create

Create these files in `Data/Models/`:

### Patient.cs
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Patient
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Species { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Breed { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public decimal Weight { get; set; }
    public string OwnerName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string OwnerPhone { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string OwnerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime RegisteredDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public List<MedicalRecord> MedicalRecords { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Invoice> Invoices { get; set; } = new();
}
```

### MedicalRecord.cs
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class MedicalRecord
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime Date { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Treatment { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Veterinarian { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

### Appointment.cs
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public enum AppointmentStatus
{
    Scheduled,
    Completed,
    Cancelled
}

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime StartTime { get; set; }
    public DateTime EndTime { get; set; }
    public string Reason { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Veterinarian { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

### Invoice.cs
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public enum PaymentStatus
{
    Pending,
    Paid,
    Cancelled
}

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public DateTime? PaidDate { get; set; }
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public PaymentStatus Status { get; set; } = PaymentStatus.Pending;
    public List<InvoiceLineItem> LineItems { get; set; } = new();
}

public class InvoiceLineItem
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public decimal Quantity { get; set; } = 1;
    public decimal UnitPrice { get; set; }
    public decimal Total => Quantity * UnitPrice;
}
```

## Update ApplicationDbContext

Edit `Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add DbSet properties for all new entities:
```csharp
public DbSet<Patient> Patients => Set<Patient>();
public DbSet<MedicalRecord> MedicalRecords => Set<MedicalRecord>();
public DbSet<Appointment> Appointments => Set<Appointment>();
public DbSet<Invoice> Invoices => Set<Invoice>();
public DbSet<InvoiceLineItem> InvoiceLineItems => Set<InvoiceLineItem>();
```

Also add using: `using VetClinic.Data.Models;`

## Create Services

Create `Services/` directory and add:

### Services/PatientService.cs
A scoped service that provides CRUD for patients and medical records:
- GetAllPatientsAsync() - includes medical records
- GetPatientByIdAsync(int id) - includes all navigations
- CreatePatientAsync(Patient patient)
- UpdatePatientAsync(Patient patient)
- DeletePatientAsync(int id)
- AddMedicalRecordAsync(MedicalRecord record)

### Services/AppointmentService.cs
- GetAppointmentsForDateAsync(DateTime date)
- GetAppointmentsByPatientAsync(int patientId)
- CreateAppointmentAsync(Appointment appointment)
- UpdateAppointmentAsync(Appointment appointment)
- CancelAppointmentAsync(int id)
- GetAvailableSlotsAsync(DateTime date) - returns available 30-min slots between 8:00-17:00, excluding already-booked times

### Services/BillingService.cs
- GetAllInvoicesAsync()
- GetInvoiceByIdAsync(int id) - include line items + patient
- GetInvoicesByPatientAsync(int patientId)
- CreateInvoiceAsync(Invoice invoice)
- ProcessPaymentAsync(int invoiceId)
- CancelInvoiceAsync(int invoiceId)

All services should use constructor-injected ApplicationDbContext and be registered as Scoped in Program.cs.

After creating all files, add the service registrations to Program.cs right before `var app = builder.Build();`:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<PatientService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped<AppointmentService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped<BillingService>();
```

With the using: `using VetClinic.Services;`

Do NOT run migrations or build — just create the files correctly.

